{
  "text": "The embedded model, which consists of M, D and of the noise estimator L, constitutes the state predictor of the plant and disturbance. It is called the \"state predictor\", since it forecasts the state at the next time step using the current state and input values of each DT integrator (\u03a3 block). The loop from the M output port back to the M input port, passing through L and D is the Predictor Loop (PL). The main input and output of the PL are the sensor measurement y, the predicted output\u0177 m and the prediction error\u00ea m = y m \u2212\u0177 m . The performance of the state predictor is mainly described by\u00ea m , whose relation to the model error e m = y \u2212 y m and to the equivalent disturbance d y according to the EMC theory [CITATION_1] is:\u00ea",
